Algorithms are step-by-step instructions designed to solve problems or perform tasks. They are used in computers, phones, and many everyday technologies. At their core, algorithms take input, follow a set of logical rules, and produce an output. Algorithms work by following a clear sequence of steps. These can include repeating actions (loops), making decisions (if-then statements), or sorting and comparing data. Simple algorithms might sort numbers or organize a list, while complex ones can drive cars, recommend movies, or recognize faces.
Behind the scenes, programmers write algorithms in code, allowing machines to execute them quickly and accurately. The efficiency and accuracy of an algorithm are important‚Äîfaster algorithms save time and resources.
In short, algorithms are the invisible engines behind much of modern technology, helping machines make decisions and solve problems efficiently.
